   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER ONE THE INITIAL STEP IN FULFILLING THE MINISTRY OF THE NEW TESTAMENT PRIESTS OF THE GOSPEL Scripture Reading: Matt 3:1-6; 1 Tim 1:16; 1 Pet 2:9; Rom 15:16; 12:1; Col 1:28-29; 1 Pet 2:5; Luke 10:1-6; John 15:16 OUTLINE The turn from the Old Testament priestly service to the New Testament priestly service: Beginning with John the Baptist: Although he can be considered the last priest of the Old Testament, he rejected that service and turned to another service Matt 3:1-4.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>He turned to become the first priest of the gospel in the New Testament: Not offering bulls and goats as sacrifices.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>But offering as sacrifices the sinners gained through his preaching of the baptism of repentance Matt 3:5-6.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>With the gospel-preaching apostles as a pattern 1 Tim 1:16: Preaching the gospel extensively to save people and offer them to God as sacrifices 1 Pet 2:9; Rom 15:16.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Leading the saints under their care to present themselves to God as living sacrifices Rom 12:1.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>In all wisdom, presenting the saints full-grown in Christ to God Col 1:28-29.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The initial step for the believers to minister as the New Testament priests of the gospel: Being the universal priesthood, not the priesthood of a few people 1 Pet 2:5.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Visiting people for the preaching of the gospel to save sinners and offer them as sacrifices to God according to God's ordination Luke 10:1-6.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>To thus personally visit people for the preaching of the gospel being to go forth and bear fruit according to God's appointing John 15:16.</S>
   </TEXT>
